results.name: Table by antidiagonals: number of m-dimensional partitions of n up to conjugacy, for n >= 1, m >= 0.
comment: Partitions are considered as generalized Ferrers diagrams; any permutation of the axes produces a conjugate.
Transposed table is A119338. - _Max Alekseyev_, May 14 2006
